mixin demographics-tabs-content
    h4 Language
    hr
    div(layout-gt-sm='row' layout-sm='column' layout-align='center top' )
        p.pr.pl.tc-grey-800
            em Ukrainian, Lithuanian, Bulgarian, and other Eastern European communities speak &nbsp
            span(style='font-weight:bold') Russian, &nbsp
            | which makes &nbsp
            strong the Russian speaking community &nbsp
            em the second largest segment of the foreign born US population, &nbsp
            | which is estimated at 5 million people.
        div(style='width:200px')
            img(src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/svet.com/home/about-us/ru-demographics-200.png" style='width:150px;height:150px')
    h4 Household
    hr
    div(class='ml++ mr+ mb')
        p • 64% are married with an average of 1.6 children per family
        p • 57% are homeowners (compared to 41% for all US foreign born)
    h4 Income
    div(class='ml++ mr+ mb')
        p • Average Annual Household Income is $87,500.
        p • 27.4% have an income of $100,000 or higher.
    h4 Education
    div(class='ml++ mr+ mb')
        div(class='ml++')
            p The inclination of this second largest foreign-born market segment towards higher education and high-paying employment ultimately leads to higher readership.
                p • 63% of the population hold a bachelor's degree or higher
                p • 82.3% have a High School Diplomas (compared to 67% for all foreign born population).
    h4 Age Average
    div(class='ml++ mr+ mb')
        p The median age is 32.5 years (compared to 38.1 years for all foreign born).
        div(class='ml++')
            p • 33.8% are 55 years old and over
            p • 57.6% are 25-54 years old
            p • 8.6% are 0-24 years old
    h4 Employment
    div(class='ml++ mr+ mb')
        p As an educated community, Russian-Americans focus more on business ownership and post-collegiate work, which results in higher-paying employment.
        div(class='ml++')
            p • 67.5% hold managerial, technical and sales occupations (compared to 45.6% within these same areas for all foreign-born).
            p • 21.4% are employed in service occupations (compared to 31.2% for all foreign-born).
            p • 11.9% are employed as operators, fabricators and/or laborers (compared to 18.7% for all foreign-born).


